Hamilton Lane Closes Largest Fund-Of-Funds In Firm History



        By Benjamin Horney



					Law360, New York (July 25, 2016,  3:54 PM EDT) -- Hamilton Lane Advisors LLC has closed its ninth private equity fund-of-funds with $516 million in capital commitments, the Pennsylvania-headquartered private investment firm said Monday, besting its initial fundraising target by more than $100 million and marking the largest fund-of-funds in its history.Hamilton Lane Private Equity Fund IX LP drew $516 million from a group of institutional investors including pension funds, endowments and foundations, among others, significantly beating out its initial goal of raising $400 million, according to a statement. Fund IX marks the firm’s largest fund-of-funds...
				
